# Rule: Use shared ID and timestamp types

- Always use the shared primitives exported from `@/types` or the ambient declarations in `global.d.ts`.
  - Prefer `UUID`, `Identifier`, `Nullable`, `Optional`, `Positionable`, `Timestamps`, and `BaseEntity` over ad-hoc `string | null` unions.
- Do not inline `string` or `number` for entity identifiers. Alias them through `UUID`/`Identifier` or reuse existing domain models.
- When creating or updating records, use `withTimestamps` (or `createTimestamp`) instead of calling `Date.now()` directly.
- Keep new utility types in `apps/web/src/types/` and update the docs if you add or change shared primitives.
- Existing files that still rely on raw primitives should be migrated when touched; never introduce new raw ID/timestamp unions.

